and accessibility, lifestyle choices, medical conditions, and more. About 3=
% of the population suffers from an eating disorder called &#8220;binge eat=
ing.&#8221; A small-scale study is using deep-brain stimulation &#8212; a m=
ethodology generally used to treat Parkinson&#8217;s patients &#8212;  to c=
urb the mental (and physical) urge to binge eat. While only two women parti=
cipated in the study, they both reported no longer feeling the irresistible=
